A stablizer kills any remaining yeast to assure that fermentation doesn't continue.
[[Campden tablets]] are a popular stablizer.
The tables contain potassium sorbate and sodium metabisulphite
are oftan used in wine, beer, or cider to ensure fermentation does not start back up.